Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Meghan Markle says "no one in the world" loves her more than Prince Harry — and the feeling is very much mutual!⁠
⁠
"He loves me so boldly, fully," she tells Harper's Bazaar. ⁠
⁠
"He also has a different perspective because he sees media that I wouldn't. No one in the world loves me more than him, so I know he's always going to make sure that he has my back."⁠
⁠
As for the ridicule she faces, the Duchess of Sussex shares, "I love being able to… play in the sandbox with my kids and to play in the front row at a show."⁠
⁠
"I think the moment that you start making all of your personal decisions based on external judgment, then you lose your authenticity."⁠
⁠
Swipe for more from Meghan and head to the link in bio 🔗 for Harper's Bazaar's full interview, on newsstands Dec. 2⁠
⁠
(📸: Meghan Markle, Getty Images, Harper's Bazaar/Malick Bodian)"

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Colleen Hoover says the legal battle between Justin Baldoni and Blake Lively has tainted how she feels about her novel, 'It Ends With Us.'⁠
⁠
"I can't even recommend it anymore. I feel like [the lawsuit] has overshadowed it," the author tells ELLE magazine. "I'm almost embarrassed to say I wrote it."⁠
⁠
"When people ask what I do, I'm just like, 'I'm a writer. Please don't ask me what I wrote.'"⁠
⁠
Colleen will be deposed for the case in a few weeks and says that Blake and Justin's ongoing conflict "feels like a circus" and is "all-around sad."⁠
⁠
"This actually truly has impacted some of the actors' careers in huge ways... I'm just trying to stay removed from the negativity. I have my own story I could tell … but I don't want to bring attention to it, and I don't want to have to put someone else down to lift myself up."⁠
⁠
Swipe for more from Colleen and head to the link in bio 🔗 to read her full interview with ELLE.⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images, It Ends With Us)"

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Shay Mitchell is standing by her skincare line for kids.⁠
⁠
After facing backlash over her new brand Rini — which includes skincare products and face masks for kids 3 and up — Shay explained that she just wants her daughters to be part of her self-care rituals.⁠
⁠
The 'Pretty Little Liars' alum is mom to Atlas Noa, 6, and Rome, 3, and says she created the line after realizing there "wasn't anything out there I felt safe enough putting on their skin."⁠
⁠
"Skincare starts from birth. We moisturize, we soothe, we comfort their skin as newborns," she said on Today with Jenna & Friends.⁠
⁠
"This is the same thing, it's just in a different format that's just more fun and, I feel, very age appropriate."⁠
⁠⁠
(📸/🎥: Getty Images, Shay Mitchell, Today with Jenna & Friends)"

After facing backlash over her new brand Rini — which includes skincare products and face masks for kids 3 and up — Shay explained that she just wants her daughters to be part of her self-care rituals.⁠
⁠
The 'Pretty Little Liars' alum is mom to Atlas Noa, 6, and Rome, 3, and says she created the line after realizing there "wasn't anything out there I felt safe enough putting on their skin."⁠
⁠
"Skincare starts from birth. We moisturize, we soothe, we comfort their skin as newborns," she said on Today with Jenna & Friends.⁠
⁠
"This is the same thing, it's just in a different format that's just more fun and, I feel, very age appropriate."⁠
⁠⁠
(📸/🎥: Getty Images, Shay Mitchell, Today with Jenna & Friends)"

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "It's like 'Country Strong' all over again! (But hopefully with a happier ending...)⁠

⁠

⁠

⁠

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "2026 is the year of the Duffaissance. 🎶⁠
⁠
Hilary dropped her first new single in 10 years, "Mature," earlier this month — and next year, we're getting a full album:⁠
⁠
'luck...or something,' dropping Feb. 20, 2026 📀⁠
⁠
This is Hilary's first album since 2015's 'Breathe In. Breathe Out.' and of course she teased the announcement with billboards in London, Paris and — yes — even Tokyo.⁠
⁠
"I am often asked how I still have my head on straight after growing up in this industry,” she says. “The album title is my way of answering that question.⁠
⁠
"It's luck, but there's also a lot of weight in the '...or something'. Many of the things I've been through along the way are held there, and I feel like ultimately that's what’s shaped me."⁠
⁠
(📸: Lauren Dunn, Hilary Duff)"

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "The new Miss Universe is already an inspiration! 👑⁠
⁠
Miss Mexico, Fátima Bosch, has officially been crowned this year's Miss Universe — and her journey was anything but easy. The pageant queen went viral after Nawat Itsaragrisil, co-owner of the Miss Universe Organization, scolded her on a livestream. When she defended herself, he called security.⁠
⁠
Fátima and several other contestants walked out of the room as Nawat ordered them to sit down or be thrown out of the pageant.⁠
⁠
And now? Miss Mexico is Miss Universe. 💁‍♀️⁠
⁠
⏩️ Swipe to see her magical moment. (📸/🎥: Getty Images, Miss Universe, Miss Universe México)"

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Kelsey Grammer tells ET that getting to play Beast again has been "one of the great experiences of my life."⁠
⁠
The last time Kelsey really got to play Dr. Hank McCoy was nearly 20 years ago in 2006's 'X-Men: The Last Stand.' Now, he's getting to reprise the role in 'Avengers: Doomsday.'⁠
⁠
When we sat down with Kelsey to talk about his new holiday movie 'The Christmas Ring,' we had to get the scoop on his big Marvel return:⁠
⁠
𝗕𝘆𝗲, 𝗯𝘆𝗲 𝗯𝗹𝘂𝗲 𝗽𝗮𝗶𝗻𝘁: Kelsey confirmed that, like his cameo in 'The Marvels,' he's playing Beast via mo-cap and not prosthetics. "Just because it's better."⁠
⁠
𝗛𝗲𝗹𝗹𝗼, 𝗼𝗹𝗱 𝗳𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝗱𝘀: Kelsey co-stars with fellow 'X-Men' alums including Patrick Stewart, Ian McKellen and Rebecca Romijn. "And James Marsden! We never really worked together."⁠
⁠
"By the time I was in 'The Last Stand,' he had been dissolved into just his glasses floating in the air, so it was nice to see him alive!"⁠
⁠
𝗫-𝗠𝗲𝗻 🤝 𝗙𝗮𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗰 𝗙𝗼𝘂𝗿: One of the new MCU stars Kelsey most enjoyed working with? "I really had a great time Pedro Pascal. And of course, we've never interacted there before."⁠
⁠
𝗣𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗗𝗼𝗼𝗺 𝗶𝗻 𝗗𝗼𝗼𝗺𝘀𝗱𝗮𝘆: Kelsey says Robert Downey Jr. is "just a terrific fella." So, is it safe to say Beast will have scenes with Doctor Doom?⁠
⁠
"It's sort of sharing a scene. I don't want to go too far!"⁠
⁠

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Simone Biles revealed that a boob job is one of three plastic surgery procedures she's had — and now she's getting even more candid about it.⁠

👀 They are under the muscle for the "most natural look"⁠

⁠
⏩️ Swipe to hear more. (📸/🎥: Simone Biles/TikTok)"

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "'Mamma Mia! 3' is a "done deal," according to Amanda Seyfried. 🕺🎶⁠
⁠
At least, she tells us she's "pretty sure" there will be a third movie — though nothing has officially been announced yet — and she's already dreamcasting a couple more blondes to join the cast.⁠
⁠
"Maybe Sophie has a cousin she hasn't seen in a while and that could be Sabrina Carpenter! And then Sydney Sweeney could show up. There's a bunch of girls that really want to be a part of it and I am all for it!"⁠
⁠
Amanda is sure about a few things though:⁠
⁠
"I just know the three dads are going to come back and we still won't know who the dad is, because it doesn't matter. Meryl is a ghost, obviously, so she'll be around. And Julie and Christine will be back, singing and looking hot.⁠
⁠
"And we're all going to be somewhere tropical and ABBA will be playing!"⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images, Mamma Mia! Here We Go Again)⁠"

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Lili Reinhart is in her "lover girl era" — and we love that for her.⁠
⁠
Lili met her man on TikTok (after she saw a video of him making fun of 'Riverdale') and slid into his DMs. They've been IG official since 2023.⁠
⁠
She tells Marie Claire that they're currently navigating the whole long-distance thing as an actor couple. (She just shot 'The Love Hypothesis,' he's starring in Mindy Kaling's new series.)⁠
⁠
"It's deeply hard on me to be apart from the person I love. I'm a very domestic woman, and I love to be at home and sit on my couch with my person and my dog; there's nothing that brings me greater joy than that specifically."⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images, Lili Reinhart)"

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Chitty Chitty Bond Bond!⁠
⁠
Dick Van Dyke is looking back on his illustrious life and revealing the one role he regrets turning down: 007. 🤵‍♂️🍸⁠
⁠
Producer Albert Broccoli approached Dick to take over the role from Sean Connery in the late '60s/early '70s.⁠
⁠
"Cubby Broccoli came to me and said, 'Would you like to be Bond?'" Dick confirmed during a sitdown on Today.⁠
⁠
"And I said, 'Have you heard my British accent?!'"⁠
⁠
Dick now says that playing Bond would "have been a great experience," though the role ultimately went to George Lazenby for 1969's 'On Her Majesty’s Secret Service.'⁠
⁠
(📸/🎥: Getty Images, Today)"

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "This year is the 30th anniversary of 'Sense and Sensibility' — and 30 years since Kate Winslet nearly flashed King Charles. 👀⁠
⁠
Kate shared the story on 'Jimmy Kimmel Live!,' recalling that she was only 20 when she met the king — then Prince Charles — for the first time at the movie's royal premiere.⁠
⁠
"I sort of hadn't realized that we were really going to meet him," she explained. "And so I forgot about the fact that I really was wearing a kind of a transparent, lace outfit."⁠
⁠
Thankfully, it was London in February, so Kate had a coat with her.⁠
⁠
"As he's making his way towards me, I'm like, 'Nipples, nipples… nipples, oh my god!' And then someone just went, 'Coat!'... I was basically covering myself in a cape and trying to hide my nipples from the King."⁠
⁠
(📸/🎥: Getty Images, Jimmy Kimmel Live!)"

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Jon Gosselin and Stephanie Lebo are married! ⁠
⁠
The couple — who got engaged almost exactly one year ago — tied the knot on Sunday at The Barn at Silverstone in Lancaster, Pennsylvania. The two exchanged vows in front of 180 guests, including two of his eight kids, Hannah and Collin, and her daughter, Juliana.⁠
⁠
"Before I met you, I never knew what it was like to be able to look at someone and smile for no reason," Jon told his new bride. "I feel like the luckiest man in the world, because I get to grow old with my best friend and the love of my life."⁠
⁠
​The bride wore the romantic Tasha wedding gown by Eddy K. ⁠Their first dance song? "I Guess I'm in Love" by Clinton Kane, the song that Jon sent Stephanie when they started dating.
⁠
Her bridal party included seven of her closest girlfriends, while his groomsmen included 21-year-old Collin, plus Jon's brothers, new brothers-in-law and closest friends. They also had a "beer bearer" handing out beverages to guests.⁠
⁠
The newlyweds will honeymoon next year, when they set sail on a Caribbean cruise. ⁠
⁠
Head to the link in bio for an inside look at the couple's joy-filled ceremony."

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Jimmy Cliff, the legendary reggae singer best known for "I Can See Clearly Now" and "You Can Get It If You Really Want," has died at age 81.⁠
⁠
His wife, Latifa Chambers, announced his passing, sharing that Cliff died "due to a seizure followed by pneumonia."⁠
⁠
"To all his fans around the world, please know that your support was his strength throughout his whole career," she wrote on social media. "He really appreciated each and every fan for their love."⁠
⁠
In his lifetime, Cliff won GRAMMYs for Best Reggae Recording for 'Cliff Hanger' in 1985 and for Best Reggae Album for 'Rebirth' in 2013. In 2010, he was was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame.⁠
⁠
"Jimmy, my darling, may you rest in peace…" Latifa closed her message. "See you and we see you Legend."⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images)"

"Jimmy, my darling, may you rest in peace…" Latifa closed her message. "See you and we see you Legend."⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images)".

⁠

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "It's (finally) time to meet Dorothy face-to-face.⁠
⁠
Though Dorothy's face is never seen in 'Wicked: For Good,' actress Bethany Weaver shared these photos of herself fully in costume as cinema's most famous farm girl.⁠
⁠
"This has been a life changing experience, it’s changed me in so many ways and most importantly, for good," she wrote on IG. ⁠
⁠
"It's been an honour to carry the legacy of the brilliant women before me who have stepped into these shoes and embarked on the yellow brick road. I hope I have made them proud."⁠
⁠
Bethany also shared a photo of herself onset with Ethan Slater as Tin Man and Jonathan Bailey as Scarecrow. 👉️ Swipe to see it.⁠
⁠
(📸/🎥: Bethany Weaver, Getty Images)⁠"

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Kim Kardashian might not be a real-life lawyer — yet — but she'll get to keep playing one on TV!⁠
⁠
Hulu just announced that 'All's Fair' has been renewed for season 2. The new season will begin filming in spring 2026.⁠
⁠
A source previously told ET that Kim had "the best time" filming the show and "couldn't care less" about any of the bad reviews.⁠
⁠
"She knew the haters would be loud, but she's focusing on the fans who love it. She’s proud of her acting and the show. She loves Ryan and wants to do more acting in the future."⁠
⁠
(📸/🎥: All's Fair, Getty Images)"

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Josh Brolin is showing off some serious ink.⁠
⁠
Josh was spotted surfing in Santa Monica over the weekend sporting what appears to be a massive new back tattoo: A lighthouse amidst stormy seas, with the Greek word "Arete" flanked by mermaids. 🌊🧜‍♀️⁠
⁠
But is it real? 🤔⁠
⁠
Back in June, Josh was seen with an equally larger back tattoo while filming his new movie 'Whalefall' — that piece was designed by makeup artist Joel Harlow and seemed to be just for the role.⁠
⁠
⏩️ Swipe to get a closer look at the ink. Is anyone else getting Ben Affleck phoenix rising vibes?⁠
⁠
(📸: Clint Brewer Photography/North Sunset/Backgrid, TheImageDirect.com)"

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Meet the Gosselins!⁠
⁠
Jon Gosselin and Stephanie Lebo tied the knot on Sunday, saying "I do" at Silverstone's The Barn in Lancaster, Pennsylvania.⁠
⁠
"She has shown me how to be sympathetic, because I was very non-sympathetic coming out of my divorce," he told ET of his new bride. "She's just made a better me."⁠
⁠
21-year-old Collin and Hannah — two of Jon's eight kids — were there for the ceremony and family photos, with Collin even serving as one of his dad's groomsman!⁠
⁠
"Looking at this moment and realizing how freeing this is for him and how much he deserves this and how much she deserves this, that's something I won't ever forget," Collin told ET.⁠
⁠
Swipe ⏩️ for more exclusive photos from the Gosselins big day and head to the link in bio 🔗 to watch ET's full interview with the newlyweds.⁠
⁠
(📸: Katy Trefry Photography / @katytrefryphotography)"

Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "James Van Der Beek is "bouncing back," according to his wife. 💛⁠
⁠
The 'Dawson's Creek' star is battling stage 3 colorectal cancer, and to help raise money for his treatment, he's auctioning off memorabilia from his movies and TV shows.⁠
⁠
James shared a video of him wearing a 'Varsity Blues' jersey and wrote, "Thank you — for the love, the prayers, the support, and for making this jersey mean something far bigger than a movie. Endlessly grateful for all of you."⁠
⁠
His wife Kimberly Van Der Beek cheered him on in the comments, writing, "You're a wizard. Bouncing back baby!! 😍😍😍."⁠
⁠
⏩️ Swipe to find out more about the auction. (📸/🎥: Varsity Blues, James Van Der Beek)"

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Eva Green is about to discover the fate of (Aunt) Ophelia.⁠
⁠
Tim Burton has recruited another one of his muses for 'Wednesday' season 3: Eva is joining the cast as Morticia Addams' sister, Ophelia Frump.⁠
⁠
Burton previously directed the actress in 'Dark Shadows,' 'Miss Peregrine's Home for Peculiar Children' and 2019's 'Dumbo.'⁠
⁠
In season 2, we saw Ophelia from behind, standing in front of a bloody message: "Wednesday Must Die." It's safe to say this isn't going to be the bubbly aunt from the original 'Addams Family' series.⁠
⁠
"I'm thrilled to join the woefully twisted world of 'Wednesday' as Aunt Ophelia," Eva said. "This show is such a deliciously dark and witty world, I can’t wait to bring my own touch of cuckooness to the Addams family."⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images, Wednesday)"

Post_Metadata/caption:
Entertainment Tonight on Instagram: "Dick Van Dyke is proving that age is truly just a number as he heads toward his 100th birthday on Dec. 13. ⁠
⁠
The legendary actor says his real secret to staying young isn't just his active lifestyle — it's his mindset.⁠
⁠
"I never wake up in a bad mood," he tells People. "I've always thought that anger is one thing that eats up a person's insides… I never really was able to work up a feeling of hate. I think that is one of the chief things that kept me going."⁠
⁠
A real-life reminder that joy is life's real spoonful of sugar. ⁠
⁠
When asked what surprises him most about reaching 100? "The fact that I made it." 🤣⁠
⁠
And in true Dick Van Dyke fashion, he's looking at the upcoming milestone with grace and gratitude. "I don't have any fear of death for some reason… I've had such a wonderfully full and exciting life."⁠
⁠
A century of charm, optimism, and pure magic. (📸: Getty Images)"

The legendary actor says his real secret to staying young isn't just his active lifestyle — it's his mindset.⁠
⁠
"I never wake up in a bad mood," he tells People. "I've always thought that anger is one thing that eats up a person's insides… I never really was able to work up a feeling of hate. I think that is one of the chief things that kept me going."⁠
⁠
A real-life reminder that joy is life's real spoonful of sugar. ⁠
⁠
When asked what surprises him most about reaching 100? "The fact that I made it." 🤣⁠
⁠
And in true Dick Van Dyke fashion, he's looking at the upcoming milestone with grace and gratitude. "I don't have any fear of death for some reason… I've had such a wonderfully full and exciting life."⁠
⁠
A century of charm, optimism, and pure magic. (📸: Getty Images)".
